{"THERMOML_MD5_CHECKSUM":"46cad51c7b54e19b6848115ec24b1464","Citation":{"sTitle":"Enthalpy of formation of Li1+xMn2-xO4 (0 less than x less than 0.1) spinel phases","sDOI":"10.1016/j.tca.2014.11.003","TRCRefID":{"tml_elements":["yrYrPub","sAuthor1","sAuthor2","nAuthorn"],"nAuthorn":"0","sAuthor2":"rei","sAuthor1":"cup","yrYrPub":"2015"},"sAbstract":"The enthalpies of formation of Li1+xMn2 xO4 (0 less than x less than 0.1) spinel phases were measured using high temperature oxide solution calorimetry in a sodium molybdate solvent at 701 C. One commercially available LiMn2O4 powder and two Li1+xMn2 xO4 samples synthesized using the sol gel method were used for the measurements. The enthalpies of formation of the spinels from the binary constituent oxides and from the elements become more exothermic with increasing lithium content and increasing average oxidation state of the manganese cation in the range 0 less than x less than 0.1. Additionally, the lithium-rich boundary of the Li1+xMn2 xO4 phase for 0 less than x less than 0.1 was re-investigated using differential thermal analysis combined with thermogravimetric analysis.","sKeyword":["Li1+xMn2-xO4","Spinel","Oxide solution calorimetry","Enthalpy of formation","Lithium-ion battery"],"sAuthor":["Cupid, D. M.[Damian M.]","Reif, A.[Alexandra]","Seifert, H. J.[Hans J.]"],"tml_elements":["TRCRefID","eType","eSourceType","sAuthor","sPubName","yrPubYr","dateCit","sTitle","sAbstract","sKeyword","sDOI","sVol","sPage"],"eSourceType":"Original","sPage":"35-41","eType":"journal","sVol":"599","dateCit":"2020-09-29","sPubName":"Thermochim. Acta","yrPubYr":"2015"},"Compound":[{"sFormulaMolec":"Li","sStandardInChIKey":"WHXSMMKQMYFTQS-UHFFFAOYSA-N","sCommonName":["lithium"],"tml_elements":["RegNum","sStandardInChI","sStandardInChIKey","sCommonName","sFormulaMolec"],"sStandardInChI":"InChI=1S/Li","RegNum":{"nOrgNum":1,"tml_elements":["nOrgNum"]}},{"sFormulaMolec":"Mn","tml_elements":["RegNum","sStandardInChI","sStandardInChIKey","sCo